OL,3,CWireless tickets to go on sale after
OL,4,Cpromoter defends Kanye West appearance
OL,6,FIn a post on X, the CAA said the Prime
OL,7,FMinister had been right to express
OL,8,Fconcern about Wireless's decision to
OL,9,Fbook West, but added that Sir Keir was
OL,10,F"not a bystander".
OL,12,FThey said: "The Government can ban
OL,13,Fanyone from entering the UK who is not
OL,14,Fa citizen and whose presence would
OL,15,F'not be conducive to the public good'.
OL,17,F"Surely this is a clear case."
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@QO]tD@LOUyD@AOUyD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
